<TITLE>ycbcr2rgb</TITLE>
<TYPE>SIVP Toolbox</TYPE>
<DATE>August, 2006</DATE>
<SHORT_DESCRIPTION name="ycbcr2rgb">Convert a YCbCr image to the equivalent RGB image.</SHORT_DESCRIPTION>
<CALLING_SEQUENCE>
   <CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>RGB = ycbcr2rgb(YCC)</CALLING_SEQUENCE_ITEM>
</CALLING_SEQUENCE>
<PARAM>
<PARAM_INDENT>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>YCC</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   A YCbCr image (hypermat). The dimension of <TT>YCbCr</TT> should be <TT>M x N x 3</TT>,
   the type should be double and the element value range should be [0,1]. 
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_ITEM>
   <PARAM_NAME>RGB</PARAM_NAME>
   <PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   Output image, which has the same size as <TT>YCC</TT> and type of double.
   </PARAM_DESCRIPTION>
   </PARAM_ITEM>
</PARAM_INDENT>
</PARAM>
<DESCRIPTION>
<P>
   <TT>ycbcr2rgb</TT> convert a RGB image to the equivalent YCbCr image using:</P>
<DESCRIPTION_INDENT>
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>R = Y + 1.403*(Cr - 0.5)</TT>
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>G = Y - 0.344*(Cr - 0.5) - 0.714*(Cb - 0.5)</TT>
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
  <DESCRIPTION_ITEM>
    <TT>B = Y + 1.773*(Cb - 0.5)</TT>
  </DESCRIPTION_ITEM> 
</DESCRIPTION_INDENT>

<P>
 Supported classe: DOUBLE.
</P>
 
</DESCRIPTION>
<EXAMPLE><![CDATA[

    RGB = imread('lena.png');
    YCC = rgb2ycbcr(RGB);
    RGB = ycbcr2rgb(YCC);
    imshow(RGB);

]]></EXAMPLE>

